The first lady of North Korea has appeared in public for the first time since December as part of celebrations marking the birthday of the country 's founding leader Kim Il-Sung .
A grinning Ri Sol-Ju , wearing what appeared to be a wedding ring on her left hand was pictured clapping next to her smiling husband Kim Jong-un during a men 's football match at Kim Il Sung Stadium on Monday .
The match was part of a series of events celebrating the 103rd birthday of Kim